Whatever our Faith intitles us to hope for, 'tis upon this Condition, that if we have right to the precious Promiſes, we muſt cleanſe our ſelves from all filthineſs of fleſh and ſpirit, and perfect holineſs in the fear of God;
               2 Pet. 1.3, 4. and St. Peter calls the Goſpel the knowledge of him who hath called us to glory; whereby (ſaith he) are given the great and precious promiſes; that by theſe ye might he partakers of the divine nature, having eſcaped the corruption

that is in the world through luſt.
